TY  - JOUR
T1  - Decreasing Absolute Risk Aversion and Option Pricing Bounds
AU  - Basso, Antonella
AU  - Pianca, Paolo
Y1  - 1997/02/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.43.2.206
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.43.2.206
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 206
EP  - 216
VL  - 43
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper efficient bounds for the price of a call option are obtained using the decreasing absolute risk aversion (DARA) dominance rule. Such lower and upper bounds are obtained minimizing and maximizing, respectively, the objective function of a nonlinear optimization problem. An explicit formula (related to an exponential utility function) is given for the special case of three states of nature. A large number of experiments have been carried out and the numerical results support the conjecture that the same formula holds for problems with a number of states n < 3. Moreover, DARA bounds are more efficient than the bounds obtained using different criteria.
AB  - In this paper efficient bounds for the price of a call option are obtained using the decreasing absolute risk aversion (DARA) dominance rule. Such lower and upper bounds are obtained minimizing and maximizing, respectively, the objective function of a nonlinear optimization problem. An explicit formula (related to an exponential utility function) is given for the special case of three states of nature. A large number of experiments have been carried out and the numerical results support the conjecture that the same formula holds for problems with a number of states n < 3. Moreover, DARA bounds are more efficient than the bounds obtained using different criteria.
